        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 6:07PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 606 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lum, or near North Branch, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Brown City around 615 PM EDT.
Melvin around 620 PM EDT.
Peck around 630 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Lynn Township,
Roseburg, Goodland Township, Kings Mill, Burnside, and Valley Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
